        <updateDate>2020-04-01T13:22:54Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Home Lead Safety Tax Credit Act of 2020</b></p> <p>This bill allows owners of eligible dwelling units a new tax credit for up to 50% of the lead hazard reduction activity costs for each such unit in a taxable year. An <i>eligible dwelling unit</i> is any unit located in the United States that was placed in service before 1978 and the residents of which during the preceding taxable year have a cumulative adjusted gross income of less than $160,000. </p> <p>The bill (1) specifies the types of lead hazard reduction activity costs eligible for the credit, including risk assessment and abatement costs; and (2) limits the amount of the credit in any taxable year to $3,000 for specified abatement measures and $1,000 for interim lead control measures. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
